# Every gate is false by default. Plan the organization guardrail and its
# temporary time-bounded Policy Admin lease first. Then create only the project
# in a complete saved plan by enabling production project creation; keep that gate true
# thereafter. Attest project creation only after verifying its ID, number, sole
# expected creator Owner, and absence of Editor. Enable the remaining project
# bootstrap in a later complete saved plan so every authorization expression is
# known and inspectable. A clean bootstrap first installs and verifies the four
# temporary state-policy recovery bindings with state IAM reconciliation false;
# only a later complete plan enables the one-way reconciliation gate. An
# existing partial environment whose canonical policies landed keeps that gate
# true and uses only the documented five-change recovery exception. Policy and
# recovery leases expire within four hours; state-migration access expires
# within 24 hours. Create and verify the tag-scoped project-policy exception
# before foundation, evidence-backed cleanup, Owner removal, and the first WIF
# handoff. Verified recovery/removal attestations remain true after cleanup.
